                        <!-- Section Tittle -->

                        <p class="pera-top mb-40">
                            Mesothelioma is a rare and deadly form of cancer that occurs in the protective
                            lining on the inside of body cavities and the outside of internal organs that affects
                            mesothelial cells.
                        </p>

                        <h3>How is it caused?</h3>
                        <p class="pera-bottom mb-30">

                            The critical risk factor that develops mesothelioma in a person is due to exposure
                            to asbestos. Even Though Asbestos related materials have been banned in Australia since 2003
                            there do exist some cases every year of people who are being diagnosed with
                            Mesothelioma. The main reason for this is a large amount of asbestos still remains in
                            older constructions, products and is very much difficult currently to investigate it.

                        </p>
                        <h3>Types of Mesothelioma</h3>
                        <p class="pera-bottom mb-30">
                            <span>Pleural Mesothelioma</span> - A type of lung cancer that initially starts in the membrane and affects lungs.<br />
                            <span>Peritoneal Mesothelioma</span> - It develops in the lining of the abdomen.

                        </p>
                    </div>
